The paper deals with the representation and analysis of random processes with memory, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). The use of rooted trees with probabilities is a common tool in data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). The paper also discusses entropy and divergence, which are fundamental concepts in machine learning and statistics (cs.LG). The application of Pinsker's inequality is a common technique in computational complexity theory (cs.CC). Finally, the paper discusses joint and conditional distributions, which are important topics in statistical inference (cs.SI).
